{
  "page": "A Dream of Spring",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #DEDEE2; text-align:center; font-style: italic;\">A Dream of Spring</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Nocover.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Nocover.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/48/Nocover.png/200px-Nocover.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"313\" srcset=\"/images/4/48/Nocover.png 1.5x\" /></a><div>No cover details.</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:United States\">United States</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_language\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:English language\">English</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Series</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre(s)</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fantasy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fantasy\">Fantasy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Preceded&#160;by</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>A Dream of Spring</b></i> is the planned title of the seventh volume of <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>'s <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> series. The book is to follow <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i> and is intended to be the final volume of the series.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background_and_publication\">Background and publication</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Dream_of_Spring&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Background and publication\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire#Planned_novels_and_future\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">Planned novels and future</a></div>\n<p>Initially <i>A Dream of Spring</i> was given the provisional title <i>A Time For Wolves</i>. However, Martin has changed the title to <i>A Dream of Spring</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-grrm_blog_060326_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-grrm_blog_060326-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Dream_of_Spring&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:1; -moz-column-count:1; column-count:1;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-grrm_blog_060326-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-grrm_blog_060326_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"citation web\"><a href=\"/index.php/Geor